author: ABQnews Staff
title: Cross-country: Rio Rancho sweeps home Jamboree
text:
Except for Los Alamos and Albuquerque Academy, nearly every prep cross-country power in New Mexico gathered Saturday for the Rio Rancho Jamboree.
A total of 90 schools competed in three divisions: championship, big school varsity and small school varsity. Racing on its home course — and the course used for state in a couple of weeks — Rio Rancho’s boys and girls swept the championship division.
Rio Rancho’s Devin Paredes used home-course advantage to race to a 5½-second victory in the boys championship division. Amanda Mayoral of Cleveland made it a hometown sweep by winning the girls division.
